---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 5 — "FLP impossibility + escape hatch" (Level 8).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). References the shared #arw arrowhead marker
 * rendered once by <Defs />. Lives as an .astro component because inline SVG with
 * kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 130"
        role="img"
        aria-label="FLP: no deterministic protocol guarantees consensus in a fully asynchronous system if one node may crash; real systems add timeouts and randomness"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">FLP (1985) — the computation cousin of Two Generals</text
            >
            <rect x="14" y="34" width="262" height="80" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="145"
                y="56"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a2218">fully async + 1 crash possible</text
            >
            <text x="145" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >no <em>deterministic</em> protocol</text
            >
            <text x="145" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >can <em>guarantee</em> consensus</text
            >
            <line x1="278" y1="74" x2="312" y2="74" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <rect x="314" y="34" width="232" height="80" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="430"
                y="56"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#244a2e">escape hatch</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e"
                >timeouts (partial synchrony)</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e"
                >+ randomness → liveness in practice</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Safety holds <em>always</em>; liveness is achieved only when the network is calm. Real
        consensus bets the network is eventually well-behaved. (Fischer, Lynch &amp; Paterson,
        1985.)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
